        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Hindu Colony Chellamal Vidyalaya - Nanganallur"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Durgalakshmi R"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-01-14",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "1. Polite teaching staffs and non-teaching staffs\n2. Big play area with practice nets, Volley ball court and sports equipment\n3. Spacious auditorium\n4. Maximum 45 students for 1 teacher in Higher classes as well\n5. Clean classrooms and restrooms (Cleaned daily after school hours)\n6. No donation, reasonable fees\n7. Cycle stand, 2 big gates and a small gate.\n8. 2 computer labs, 1 chemistry, physics, biology lab and 1 library with good collection of books and guides\n9. 4 buildings and maximum 3 floors in each (not too many steps)\n10. Excellent tutoring\n11. Good canteen facility\n12. Coaching classes are conducted for weak performers in academics\n13. Brief Parent - teacher meeting is conducted every year once or twice\n14. Students are encouraged to speak English inside the campus. Spoken English classes are held regularly in primary and secondary school\n15. Opportunities in various extra curricular activities are given to the right students, regardless of their academic performance\n16. Theme - based Science Annual exhibition conducted every year\n17. Various Intra school competitions are conducted and the winners and runners of which are awarded on the Annual day celebrations, along with the general proficiency holders. Sports competition winners and runners are awarded on the Sports day celebrations.\n18. Separate Boys and girls volleyball team and the team participated in various inter school tournaments. Inter school volleyball tournament is conducted every year\n19. Shraddha Vibushita - Children's day celebration completely organised by class 11 students for the students in primary and secondary levels. Various events are organised and certificated are awarded. Similarly teacher's day is celebrated every year on 5th September, organised by students of class 11, for teachers at all level\n20. Guest lectures are conducted from time to time.",
